    <details class="faq-item"><summary>What is the Health Insurance Marketplace?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>The Health Insurance Marketplace is a government-run platform created by the Affordable Care Act where you can compare and purchase health insurance plans. Plans are standardized into metal tiers (Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum) so you can compare coverage and costs. Depending on your income, you may qualify for premium tax credits that reduce your monthly payment and cost-sharing reductions that lower deductibles and copays. The federal marketplace at HealthCare.gov serves most states, while some states run their own exchanges.</p></div></details>
